Question 12: Code a for loop that cycles through all the characters of a string represented by a variable and assigns each character to an element of an array that has been declared beforehand.
Answer 12: for (var i = 0; i < text.length; i++) {
textArray[i] = text.charAt(i);
}

Question 18: Concatenate the first character of a string represented by a variable with the last character of another string represented by a variable and assign the combination to a variable that hasn't been declared beforehand.
Answer: var combo = str1.charAt(0) + str2.charAt(str2.lenght - 1);

